%% Data Flow Diagram - ODH Notebook Controller (kubeflow)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Mutating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS (service-ca)
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy) 443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS (service-ca)
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation (with auth)
    User->>APIServer: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>Auth: API server cert
    Webhook->>APIServer: GET ImageStream (resolve image)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>Webhook: ImageStream data
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Mutated Notebook<br/>(kube-rbac-proxy sidecar, CA certs,<br/>proxy env vars injected)
    APIServer-->>User: Notebook created

    Note over Controller,APIServer: Controller reconciliation
    APIServer->>Controller: Watch event (Notebook)
    Controller->>APIServer: Create HTTPRoute in controller ns<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>APIServer: Create ReferenceGrant in user ns<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>APIServer: Create NetworkPolicy, Service,<br/>SA, ClusterRoleBinding, ConfigMap<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>Controller: Resources created

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Accessing Notebook (with kube-rbac-proxy)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>Encryption: TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token forwarded
    KRBAC->>APIServer: SubjectAccessReview<br/>verb=get, resource=notebooks<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>KRBAC: Allowed/Denied
    KRBAC->>Notebook: Proxy to localhost<br/>Port: 8888/TCP HTTP<br/>Headers: X-Auth-Request-User,<br/>X-Auth-Request-Groups
    Notebook-->>KRBAC: Response
    KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response (HTTPS)
    Gateway-->>User: Response (HTTPS)

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: User Accessing Notebook (without auth)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>No Auth<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Notebook: Forward to notebook service<br/>Port: 8888/TCP HTTP<br/>No Auth
    Notebook-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Response (HTTPS)

    Note over Controller,APIServer: Flow 4: Elyra Pipeline Config Sync
    Controller->>APIServer: GET DSPA CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>Controller: DSPA status (API endpoint)
    Controller->>APIServer: GET Gateway CR (hostname)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>Controller: Gateway hostname
    Controller->>APIServer: GET S3 credential Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    APIServer-->>Controller: S3 credentials
    Controller->>APIServer: CREATE/UPDATE ds-pipeline-config Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
